\n{{for|the players drafted by Houston Rockets|List of Houston Rockets first and second round draft picks}}\n{{Houston Rockets roster}}\n\n===Retained draft rights===\nThe Rockets hold the draft rights to the following unsigned draft picks who have been playing outside the NBA. A drafted player, either an international draftee or a college draftee who is not signed by the team that drafted him, is allowed to sign with any non-NBA teams. In this case, the team retains the player's draft rights in the NBA until one year after the player's contract with the non-NBA team ends.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbafaq.com/salarycap.htm|title=NBA Salary Cap FAQ \u2013 2011 Collective Bargaining Agreement|quote=If the player is already under contract to, or signs a contract with a non-NBA team, the team retains the player's draft rights for one year after the player's obligation to the non-NBA team ends. Essentially, the clock stops as long as the player plays pro ball outside the NBA.|first=Larry|last=Coon|authorlink=Larry Coon|accessdate=April 13, 2014}}</ref> This list includes draft rights that were acquired from trades with other teams.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:90%;\"\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Draft\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Round\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Pick\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Pos.\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Nationality\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Current team\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Note(s)\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"{{NBA color cell|Houston Rockets}};\"|Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2009 NBA draft|2009]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|34\n| {{sortname|Sergio|Llull}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|G\n| {{flagu|Spain}}\n| [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] ([[Liga ACB|Spain]])\n| Acquired from the [[Denver Nuggets]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/rockets/news/Rockets_Nab_Three_Players_in_D-317489-34.html|title=Houston purchases trio of second-round picks|date=June 26, 2009|work=NBA.com|accessdate=April 15, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2008 NBA draft|2008]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|54\n| {{sortname|Maarty|Leunen}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|F\n| {{flagu|United States}}\n| [[Fortitudo Pallacanestro Bologna|Lavoropi\u00f9 Fortitudo Bologna]] ([[Serie A2 Basket|Italy]])\n| Re-acquired from the [[Dallas Mavericks]] (via [[Los Angeles Clippers|L.A. Clippers]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks Get Center Chinanu Onuaku in Trade With Rockets |url=https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/sports/Mavericks-Get-Center-Chinanu-Onuaku-in-Trade-With-Rockets-489926141.html |website=www.nbcdfw.com|accessdate=August 1, 2018 |date=August 1, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2008 NBA draft|2008]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|53\n| {{sortname|Tadija|Dragi\u0107evi\u0107}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|F\n| {{flagu|Serbia}}\n| [[CB Breog\u00e1n|Caf\u00e9s Candelas Breog\u00e1n]] ([[Liga ACB|Spain]])\n| Acquired from the [[Chicago Bulls]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite tweet| user=ShamsCharania |number=1087816430731624448 |date=January 22, 2019 |title=Sources: Rockets and Bulls have completed trade: Carmelo Anthony, draft rights to Jon Diebler and $1.56 million to Chicago for draft rights to Tadija Dragicevoc.}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2005 NBA draft|2005]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|52\n| {{sortname|Axel|Hervelle}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|F\n| {{flagu|Belgium}}\n| [[Spirou Charleroi|Proximus Spirou]] ([[Pro Basketball League|Belgium]])\n| Acquired from the [[Denver Nuggets]]