AA|Tipperary]]\n|1925-1926\n|[[1925 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1925]]\n|{{Birth date|1898|1|16|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|1988|11|29|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1898|1|16|1988|11|29}}\n|-\n|\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Art Foley]]\n|[[Wexford GAA|Wexford]]\n|1946-1957\n|[[1955 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1955]], [[1956 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1956]]\n|{{Birth date|1928|12|14|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|2019|10|28|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1928|12|14|2019|10|28}}\n|-\n|\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Denis O'Gorman]]\n|[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|1934-1942\n|[[1937 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1937]]\n|{{Birth date|1914|8|28|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|2005|5|1|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1914|8|28|2005|5|1}}\n|-\n|\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Tom Wall (hurler)|Tom Wall]]\n|[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|1936-1945\n|[[1945 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1945]]\n|{{Birth date|1914|8|19|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|2005|4|15|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1914|8|19|2005|4|15}}\n|-\n|\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Tom Dwan]]\n|[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|1912-1924\n|[[1916 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1916]]\n|{{Birth date|1889|11|22|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|1980|5|17|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1889|11|22|1980|5|17}}\n|-\n|\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Din Joe Buckley]]\n|[[Cork GAA|Cork]]\n|1940-1949\n|[[1941 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1941]], [[1942 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1942]], [[1943 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1943]], [[1944 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1944]], [[1946 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1946]]\n|{{Birth date|1919|6|30|df=yes}}\n|{{death date|2009|10|8|df=yes}} \n|{{age in years and days|1919|6|30|2009|10|8}}\n|}\n\n====Disciplinary====\nJust six players have ever been sent off in an All-Ireland final: [[Tom Ryan (Killenaule hurler)|Tom Ryan]] of Tipperary and [[Lar Foley]] of Dublin in the [[1961 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship Final|1961 final]], [[\u00c9amonn Scallan]] of [[Wexford GAA|Wexford]] in the [[1996 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship Final|1996 final]] against [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]] (sent off in the 34th minute); [[Benny Dunne]] of [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] in the [[2009 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship Final|2009 final]] and [[Cyril Donnellan]] of [[Galway GAA|Galway]] in the [[2012 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship Final|2012 final]] replay and\n[[Richie Hogan]] of [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] in the [[2019 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship Final|2019 final]]\n\n==Managers==\n\n===Records===\n\n* [[Brian Cody]] is the only manager to win the All-Ireland title eleven times, in 2000, 2002, 2003, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009, 2011, 2012, 2014, 2015 (all [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]]).\n* Just two managers have reached the All-Ireland final with two different teams: \n** [[Babs Keating|Michael \"Babs\" Keating]] with [[Galway GAA|Galway]] (1979) and [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] (1988, 1989, 1991).\n** [[Davy Fitzgerald]] with [[Waterford GAA|Waterford]] (2008) and [[Clare GAA|Clare]] (2013).\n* In 2009, [[Justin McCarthy (hurler)|Justin McCarthy]] became the first manager to reach the All-Ireland semi-finals with three different teams: [[Cork GAA|Cork]] (1975, 1984), [[Waterford GAA|Waterford]] (2002, 2004, 2006, 2007) and [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]] (2009). In addition, he was in charge of [[Clare GAA|Clare]] in the 1978 [[Munster Senior Hurling Championship|Munster]] final, when a win would have qualified them directly for the all-Ireland final.\n* Fourteen individuals have won the All-Ireland as a player then later as a manager:\n** [[Johnny Clifford]] of [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won as a player in 1954 and as a manager in 1986.\n** [[Ollie Walsh]] of [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] won as a player in 1957, 1963, 1967 and 1969 and as a manager in 1992, and 1993.\n** [[Michael Keating (hurler)|Michael \"Babs\" Keating]] of [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] won as a player in 1964, 1965 and 1971 and as a manager in 1989 and 1991.\n** [[Eddie Keher]] of [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] won as a player in 1963, 1967, 1969, 1972, 1974 and 1975 and as a co-manager in 1979.\n** [[Justin McCarthy (hurler)|Justin McCarthy]] of [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won as a player in 1966 and as a co-manager in 1984.\n** [[Pat Henderson]] of [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] won as a player in 1967, 1969, 1972, 1974 and 1975 and as a manager in 1979, 1982 and 1983.\n** [[Brian Cody]] of [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] won as a player in 1975, 1982 and 1983 and as a manager in 2000, 2002, 2003, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009, 2011, 2012, 2014, 2015\n** [[Jimmy Barry-Murphy]] of [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won as a player in 1976, 1977, 1978, 1984 and 1986 and as a manager in 1999.\n** [[John Allen (hurling manager)|John Allen]] of [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won as a player in 1978 and as a manager in 2005.\n** [[D\u00f3nal O'Grady]] of [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won as a player in 1984 and as a manager in 2004.\n** [[Nicky English]] of [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] won as a player in 1989 and 1991 and as a manager in 2001.\n** [[Davy Fitzgerald]] of [[Clare GAA|Clare]] won as a player in 1995 and 1997 and as a manager in 2013.\n** [[Eamonn Cregan]] of [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]] won as a player in 1973 and as a manager with Offaly in 1994.\n** [[Michael Ryan (hurler, born 1970)|Michael Ryan]] of [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] won as a player in 1991 and as a manager in 2016\n\n==Team results table==\nThis section represents in colour-coded tabular format the results of [[GAA county teams]] in the [[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship]] since [[1997 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|1997]]. \n\nPrior to 1997, counties played in separate [[provincial championships]], with only four provincial champions coming together in the All-Ireland semi-finals, and it is difficult to directly compare results across counties. Since 1997, several beaten teams from the provincial championships play together in the All-Ireland qualifier series.\n\n===Table===\n; Current\n* {{bg|red|'''Ch'''}} \u2014 Champions\n* {{bg|orange|RU}} \u2014 Runners-up\n* {{bg|yellow|SF}} \u2014 All-Ireland semi-finals (3rd\u20134th place)\n* {{bg|#90EE90|QF}} \u2014 All-Ireland quarter-finals (5th\u20136th place)\n* {{bg|#ADD8E6|PQF}} \u2014 All-Ireland preliminary quarter-finals (7th\u20138th place)\n* {{bg|#E0B0FF|Lrr4}} {{bg|#E0B0FF|Mrr4}} \u2014 Leinster/Munster round robin, 4th place (9th\u201310th place)\n* {{bg|#D3D3D3|Lrr5}} {{bg|#D3D3D3|Mrr5}} \u2014 Leinster/Munster round robin, 5th place  (11th\u201312th place)\n* \u2014 \u2014 did not compete\n* \u2665 \u2014 Munster champions\n* \u2666 \u2014 Leinster champions\n\n===Past===\n\n*The All-Ireland championship has used many different competition structures since 1997, and it is not always obvious how to rank teams. In general, the colouring code for champions (red), runners-up (orange) and semi-finalists (yellow) holds true. After that, teams are shaded green, blue, purple and grey in descending order of performance. \n*The [[Ulster Senior Hurling Championship]] has not had any bearing on the All-Ireland championship since [[2005_All-Ireland_Senior_Hurling_Championship|2005]] so it is not included from that year onward.\n*Changes of provincial championship:\n**[[Galway GAA|Galway]] competed in the [[Connacht Senior Hurling Championship]] until [[1998_All-Ireland_Senior_Hurling_Championship|1998]]; they have played in the [[Leinster Senior Hurling Championship]] since [[2009 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2009]]\n**[[Kerry GAA|Kerry]] competed in the [[Munster Senior Hurling Championship]] until [[2004_All-Ireland_Senior_Hurling_Championship|2004]]; they have played in the [[Leinster Senior Hurling Championship]] since [[2016 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2016]]\n**[[Antrim GAA|Antrim]] still compete in the [[Ulster Senior Hurling Championship]], however, it has not been part of the All-Ireland since [[2004_All-Ireland_Senior_Hurling_Championship|2004]]; they have played in the [[Leinster Senior Hurling Championship]] since [[2009 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2009]]\n**[[London GAA|London]] competed in the [[Ulster Senior Hurling Championship]] until [[2004_All-Ireland_Senior_Hurling_Championship|2004]]; they played in the [[Leinster Senior Hurling Championship]] in [[2013 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2013]] and [[2014 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2014]]\n\nAbbreviations used:\n* \u2663 \u2014 Ulster champions\n* \u2660 \u2014 Connacht champions\n*QF \u2014 All-Ireland quarter-finalists\n*QR3 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, round 3\n*QR2 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, round 2\n*QR1 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, round 1\n*Qp3 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, phase 3\n*Qp2 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, phase 2\n*Qp1 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, phase 1\n*Qpr \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, preliminary round\n*Qrr3 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, round robin, 3rd place\n*Qrr4 \u2014 All-Ireland qualifiers, round robin, 4th place\n*Uf \u2014 Ulster finalists\n*Usf \u2014 Ulster semi-finalists\n*Uqf \u2014 Ulster quarter-finalists\n*Lsf \u2014 Leinster semi-finalists\n*Lqf \u2014 Leinster quarter-finalists\n*L1r \u2014 Leinster first round\n*Lpr \u2014 Leinster preliminary round\n*Lpr2 \u2014 Leinster second preliminary round\n*Lpr1 \u2014 Leinster first preliminary round\n*Lpqr \u2014 Leinster preliminary quarter-final\n*Lrr2 \u2014 Leinster round robin, 2nd place\n*Lrr3 \u2014 Leinster round robin, 3rd place\n*Lrr4 \u2014 Leinster round robin, 4th place\n*Lsf \u2014 Munster semi-finalists\n*Lqf \u2014 Munster quarter-finalists\n* Cf \u2014 Connacht finalists\n*Rsf \u2014 won relegation semi-final\n*Rf \u2014 won relegation final\n*Rel \u2014 relegated to [[Christy Ring Cup]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%;\"\n|-\n! County\n! {{abbr|Pr.|Provincial championship \u2014 Connacht, Leinster, 